The paper discusses a decision tree for designers to judge the suitability of a P2P architecture for their applications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the characteristics of P2P systems, which could also place it in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Security and Privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper may also be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category, as P2P systems often involve social interactions between peers. Finally, the paper may be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category, as it discusses a decision tree heuristic.
